Hello! How can I assist you today?
Thanks for providing the campaign ID. Could you please let me know what specific issue or question you have regarding this campaign? I'll do my best to assist you!
I paused this campaign at 14 clicks bcuz cpc is very high

I understand your concern about the high CPC. To optimize your campaign, you might consider adjusting your bidding strategy or targeting options. You can also try using our bid estimation tool to identify ad sets with high growth potential and project conversion metrics based on bid rate adjustments. If you need more detailed guidance, feel free to check out our tCPA Best Practices article here: [tCPA Best Practices](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/18020232662797-tCPA-Best-Practices). Let me know if you have any other questions!

It seems like your campaign might be in the learning phase, which typically completes after around 20-30 conversions. During this time, minimal changes should be made to allow the system to analyze performance signals and find the best audience segments. If your campaign stopped at 25 clicks, it might be due to the system trying to maintain efficiency. You can consider increasing your bid rate or switching back to Max Conversion bidding if you want more volume. For more detailed strategies, you can refer to our Newsbreak Ads Overview article here: [Newsbreak Ads Overview](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/18020232662797-tCPA-Best-Practices). Let me know if you need further assistance!

I'm sorry to hear that you're experiencing issues with your campaign. To help manage costs and improve performance, you might want to review your targeting options and creative assets. Additionally, consider adjusting your daily budget or bid strategy to better align with your goals. If you haven't already, you can also check the weekly performance overview to identify trends and areas for improvement. For more detailed strategies, please refer to our [tCPA Best Practices](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/18020232662797-tCPA-Best-Practices) article. If you need further assistance, feel free to reach out!
